what would you have done i was called in for a job today by a job agency they said i can trun up in the afternoon today and work all tuesday and wednesday the job sounded rubbish but a job is a job i went there after a minute drive and they said i couldn't work as i had no safety boots on they said to come back tomorrow with them the agency never told me to bring them so i was very annoyed as it wasted the middle part of my day and petrol too i was so annoyed that i told the agency that i didn't want to work on tuesday or wednesday either as i was very unhappy about the situation i'm a student on my summer break so a job is not a must but it would be useful i have just been messed around by agencies so many times i that it has got me to an annoyed stage would you have still worked the other two days or would you have done the same as me join another agency they should have told you of any special equipment you needed and a good pair of boots could be sixty quid plus so not many people buy them on the off chance i wouldn't go back after that first experience join another agency Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina Civil engineering and infrastructure repair in New Orleans after Hurricane Katrina Knots Landing Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March STS-59 UK fuel protests Effect of Hurricane Katrina on New Orleans Ocean's Twelve Shaggy dog story Pitaten Blur Pittsburgh Steelers James T. Aubrey, Jr. The Smoking Room Our Friends in the North Paul Is Dead American Dreams One Tree Hill (TV series) Poker jargon Brian Close Married... with Children Dawson's Creek Shawn Michaels Social rule Friends Wednesday EastEnders SWAT Badly Drawn Kitties Midnight Run John Layfield Operation Market Garden Software engineering Reservoir Dogs Time Out of Mind STS-61 Opportunity rover timeline for 2004 March Major League Baseball television contracts Jayson Blair 2000 Australian Grand Prix Opportunity rover timeline for 2004 February Dream Job (Season 2) 2005 Kashmir earthqu